  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.4,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "- [David] Hello,\nwordsmith. Ah, one second."
      },
      {
        "start": 2.5,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "(hissing)"
      },
      {
        "start": 3.7,
        "duration": 4.3,
        "text": "Hi, sorry, I was just doing\nsome deep sea diving for words."
      },
      {
        "start": 7.9,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "I brought you two treasures from the deep:"
      },
      {
        "start": 10.3,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "submerge and profound."
      },
      {
        "start": 12.7,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "Let's define these words,\nlook at their origins,"
      },
      {
        "start": 14.7,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "and then use each word in a sentence."
      },
      {
        "start": 16.8,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "Let me put my diving\nsuit away. One second."
      },
      {
        "start": 18.6,
        "duration": 1.3,
        "text": "(diving suit clattering)"
      },
      {
        "start": 19.9,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "First, submerge, a verb."
      },
      {
        "start": 21.9,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "To submerge is to go underwater"
      },
      {
        "start": 24.1,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "or to put something underwater,"
      },
      {
        "start": 26.1,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "like I submerged the French\nfry in a lake of ketchup."
      },
      {
        "start": 30.3,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "Profound is an adjective,\nand it means deep"
      },
      {
        "start": 33.3,
        "duration": 4.0,
        "text": "or intensely felt, showing deep\nunderstanding or intellect,"
      },
      {
        "start": 37.3,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "as in my explanation of the origins"
      },
      {
        "start": 39.9,
        "duration": 3.7,
        "text": "of the word profound will be profound."
      },
      {
        "start": 43.6,
        "duration": 4.5,
        "text": "So let's take a deep dive,\nhah, into these words' origins."
      },
      {
        "start": 48.1,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "Submerge, sub is a Latin\nprefix meaning below,"
      },
      {
        "start": 51.2,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "like subscribe, write your name under here"
      },
      {
        "start": 54.5,
        "duration": 1.3,
        "text": "so I can send you videos,"
      },
      {
        "start": 55.7,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "or substandard, it's not very good,"
      },
      {
        "start": 58.0,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "it's below the standard."
      },
      {
        "start": 59.5,
        "duration": 3.6,
        "text": "Or submarine under the\nmarine, under the sea,"
      },
      {
        "start": 63.1,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "where the underwater boat goes."
      },
      {
        "start": 65.3,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "And then merge means to plunge."
      },
      {
        "start": 71.5,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "The root there is merg."
      },
      {
        "start": 74.6,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "So to submerge is to plunge\nbelow, splash beneath the water,"
      },
      {
        "start": 79.6,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "although you could submerge"
      },
      {
        "start": 81.1,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "in any kind of plungeable liquid,"
      },
      {
        "start": 84.0,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "like fries into ketchup\nin the earlier example."
      },
      {
        "start": 87.3,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "Now, turning to profound,"
      },
      {
        "start": 89.8,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "we have pro, meaning towards,"
      },
      {
        "start": 93.2,
        "duration": 2.0,
        "text": "and found, or sometimes fund"
      },
      {
        "start": 96.6,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "from Latin meaning bottom."
      },
      {
        "start": 99.9,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "So something profound is deep."
      },
      {
        "start": 102.6,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "It's going to the bottom of things."
      },
      {
        "start": 104.8,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "We can use it to mean literally deep,"
      },
      {
        "start": 106.6,
